This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it proposes a novel approach for sequence decoding specifically for the task of abstractive summarization. The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in the field of deep learning and machine learning, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a discriminator to drive sequence generation, which is a common technique in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural Networks (cs.NE), making these sub-categories also likely.
